2 + (b1 - b2)^2 )<br><br>With that out of the way ..<br><br>1) It's still hider's stealth compared to seeker's level.  The difference is the multiplier used to determine detect radius.  (level - stealth)  If level is higher than hider's stealth, the multiplier is 0.<br><br>2) There is a &quot;minimum detect radius&quot; of 125. This distance is the radius if hider's stealth is equal to or greater than seeker's level.<br><br>3) For each level higher than hider's stealth, the detect radius is increased by 50 (for detect hidden characters), or by 20 (for non-detect-hidden characters).  Net effect, when seeker's level is higher than hider's stealth, detection radius is mininum detect radius + ( multiplier * radius increase ).<br><br>Examples:<br>Level 35 seeker (non-detect-hidden), level 39 hider (stealth 30)<br>Detect radius = ((35 - 30) * 20) + 125 = 225<br><br>Level 50 seeker (detect hidden), level 50 hider (stealth 45)<br>Detect radius = ((50 - 45) * 50) + 125 = 375<br><br>Level 45 seeker (non-detect-hidden), level 50 hider (stealth 50)<br>Detect radius = ((45 - 50) * 20) + 125 = 125 (remember stealth above seeker's level results in radius addition of 0)<br><br>4) Minimum detect distance is the same for detect hidden and non-detect-hidden characters.  I have STRONGLY suggested that this minimum detect distance be doubled for detect hidden capable characters.<br><br>---<br><br>Net effect:<br>For characters that are higher level than the stealth level of the person hidden, detect hidden grants a 2.5x range per (level - stealth) difference advantage to the detect hidden class, if level is greater than stealth.<br><br>For characters that are the same level or lower than the stealth level of the person hiding, there is no advantage to having detect hidden.  The minimum detection radius is the same for all characters in this situation.<br><br>---<br><br>As stated above, I have suggested that the minimum detection radius be doubled for characters with detect hidden, because eventually we will all be level 50 and if it remains as is, there is no advantage to detect hidden capable characters.  <br><br>The new changes detecting people below your level in stealth skill are good, clearly giving the advantage to the detect hidden class.  With a minor tweak to min detect distance for detect hidden characters, I think this skill will be complete, and useful for those that receive it.<br> <p>-- Huff McTuff, 39 Nightshade, Pendragon<br>-- <i>Nightshade Team Lead</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaithcaidh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caith Caidh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 1:29:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Detect Hidden test results, v1.45b</span><hr size=1> Interesting... Any idea if the z axis is included in those calculations at all?  ie, will someone at the top of the keep wall, looking down, be able to see an assassin who just reached the base and is about to climb, merely because their x, y coords are near?<br><br>-Caith <p><IMG SRC="http://www.dopplex.net/sigfile2.jpg" ALT="Caith Caidh, 35th Season Nightshade, An Claidheamh Soluis" ALIGN="middle"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uannid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anni D</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 1:45:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Detect Hidden test