esafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 2:08:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> I could see this helping out a 50 assassin finding lower level archers.. but not much else. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 2:26:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> Did they have much trouble finding lower level archers to begin with?  <br><br>They ought to have made detect hidden work like the spell in EQ... and how long it lasts depends on your stealth level vs. their stealth... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usquinkmcpoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Squink McPoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 2:29:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..</span><hr size=1> No, 51 stealth isn't absolute invisibility.<br><br>Anything over 50 if they keep current implementation, will not help you in RvR vs. other players.  The effect on run speed and mob 'too close to hide' radius has yet to be determined over spec 50, but that's not the point of this post.<br><br>Maybe I worded it wrong, but if you have stealth at or above the seeker's level and you are stealthed, they can see you within the minimum detection range.  Points in stealth above their level do not change this minimum detection range in all tests that I performed.<br><br>Hence, extrapolate to the &quot;everyone is level 50 scenario&quot; .. with you being stealthed with an assumed 50 spec with items, everyone can see you within the minimum detection range.<br><br>There are still client/datastream issues (like how data sent that 'pops' a stealthed character into transparent mode, but first renders them fully visible for a split-second, is only sent every 3ish seconds, so moving at a full run you may never see a stealthed character even if you are in range to see them, unless you pause long enough for the 3 second data to get sent).  I've mentioned those issues to the devs as well, but my first impression is that those aren't as easy to fix as simply making detect hidden classes have an extended minimum detection radius.  Although they are still valid concerns that do affect the skill. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uannid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anni D</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 2:29:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> I don't think it should be absolute.<br><br>It really looks like they have the right idea, but it should be based off skill, the detect hidden classes starting off with about double the range of non detect hidden, and gaining ground about twice as fast.<br><br>The way they have it now, is as a friend says, &quot;jacked&quot;<br><br>-Anni <p>A.K.A.MoonflowerNightshade/SeamstressHibernia-Guinivere</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usquinkmcpoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Squink McPoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 2:37:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> Present 1.45b detect hidden just about has it right, in my opinion.  They just need to double the minimum detect radius for detect hidden characters and then I think it would be just right.<br><br>In 1.45b, we gain ground (if our level is higher than the stealthed person's stealth skill) 2.5x as fast as a non-detect hidden class.<br><br>Btw, the formula I have worked out was figured out by me from the data, they never told us exactly how it works.  So, I wanted to say up front that I could be wrong.  I don't think that I am, but it's not outside the realm of possibility.  I'm too much of a math/numbers nerd. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uannid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anni D</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 2:47:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> Yes, it would be great, provided it was based off your stealth skill, and not your level.<br><br>I really think that your actual skill level should be much more important. But then again, more archers will be max'd than assassins because they farm RPs so easily they will reach their max levels in all skills far before any assassin does unless they actually pay for the skill into mid 40s.<br><br>Also I really do feel, like you, that detect hidden people should be given an initial lead on the non detect classes, otherwise the skill becomes worthless at 50.<br><br>-Anni <p>A.K.A.MoonflowerNightshade/SeamstressHibernia-Guinivere</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uannid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anni D</A> at: 2/1/02 2:48:25 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvalarauco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valarauco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 3:16:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~bdemong/valaface.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> Agree on the min detect range due to the 'level 50 problem'.<br><br>Question: can you give a general idea of how physically far these numbers are?  That is, 125, 50, and 20.  I have no point of reference and I haven't taken the time to learn the coordinate system in this game (landmarks work extremely well).  I could log in and check but you probably know off the top of your head.<br><br>Also, pointing something out because I think a few people missed it:<br><br>The distance non-detect sees a person at versus a detect person, with...<br><br>...1 level higher than stealth skill of hider, 145 vs 175<br>...2 levels higher than stealth skill of hider, 165 vs 225<br>...5 levels higher than stealth skill of hider, 225 vs 375<br>...10 levels higher than stealth skill of hider, 325 vs 625<br>...20 levels higher than stealth skill of hider, 525 vs 1125<br><br>No opinion on that, just pointing it out.  We don't see stealthed people 2.5x as far away as someone without detect hidden; it starts even, and gets exponentially more, working out to near 2x as the disparity increases.  If our minimum chance were doubled (to 250), it would start at double and go up from there, instead of starting even and approaching double.  Nevermind, I have an opinion: the latter is definitely how it should be.<br><br>Also, afterthought: it kinda seems like Stealth was balanced for archers (who stay at a range at all times if they can) rather than assassins (who purposely put themselves in melee range). <p><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~bdemong/valarauco.gif"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvalarauco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valarauco</A> at: 2/1/02 4:00:00 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usneekeerz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sneekeerz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 3:57:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Detect Hidden test results, v1.45b</span><hr size=1> I hope this will not be ANOTHER fluff fix for us, I'm really looking foward to this one.<br>As of right now, as a lvl 44 Infiltrator, I have no problem finding blue and below hidden players. Its those big badass archers with 50 stealth that I want to find. From your testing Huff, i think things will remain pretty much the same for us, still wont be able to find archers around my lvl unless they gimp thier stealth, which most archers dont. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usquinkmcpoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Squink McPoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 4:58:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> I meant to include a point of reference so that '125' means something, but my notes are missing it.<br><br>Rough estimate: a human-sized horse (the ones britons/norse/celts ride) are approx 200 in length, based on /loc.<br><br>If anyone is bored and feels like double-checking that, feel free.  Otherwise I will get some points of reference after I get home from work. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uannid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anni D</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 5:27:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> So essentially at level 50 we will have to trip over an archer to see them? oh great. glad I took the detect hidden class. <br><br>What a great skill.<br><br>looks like I will just keep using my stealth ability to hide from archers and run away as opposed to seek them out.<br><br>-Anni <p>A.K.A.MoonflowerNightshade/SeamstressHibernia-Guinivere</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uryken.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 6:13:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> I have never liked how character level is the determining factor, as opposed to the actual Stealth skill.  I would much rather see detection be based upon Stealth levels of each character.<br><br>Simple fix (for detection purposes only):<br><br>if seeker has detect hidden<br>((target's_stealth*(target's_stealth/target's_level)) - seeker's_stealth*(seeker's_stealth/seeker's_level).<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  = effective Stealth level of target.<br><br>Some examples:<br><br>level 20 seeker 20 stealth          level 30 target with 30 stealth:  <br>(30 - 16) = target has 14 levels of stealth at level 30, or effectively slightly less than half-specc'd in Stealth.<br><br>level 20 seeker 20 stealth          level 40 target with 40 stealth:<br><br>(40 - 16) = target has 24 levels of stealth at level 40, or effectively slightly more than half-specc'd in Stealth.<br><br>level 30 seeker 30 stealth          level 30 target with 30 stealth:<br>(30 - 24) = target has 6 levels of stealth at level 30, or effectively 20% specc'd in Stealth.<br><br>level 40 seeker 30 stealth          level 30 target with 30 stealth:<br><br>(30 - 1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  = target has 12 levels of stealth at level 30, or effectively slightly less than half-specc'd in Stealth.<br><br>level 40 seeker 30 stealth          level 30 target with 20 stealth:<br><br>(13 - 1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  = target has 0 levels of stealth at 30, or effectively no spec points in Stealth.<br><br>level 40 seeker 40 stealth          level 40 target with 40 stealth:<br><br>(40 - 32) = target has 8 levels of stealth at level 40, or effectivelyl 20% spec in Stealth.<br><br><br>Couple things this system would do.  It would only be used for detection by classes which possessed Detect Hidden.  It would depend on the Stealth of the seeker *and* the target.  It would not be solely character-level based.  With both seeker and target full-specc'd, it would effectively lead to the target being 20% specc'd in Stealth at any given level.<br><br><br><br>Trenos <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usmudgedaemelar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Smudge DaeMelar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://cwmonkey.virtualave.net/s/net8/laghost.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 8:48:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> For characters that are the same level or lower than the stealth level of the person hiding, there is no advantage to having detect hidden. The minimum detection radius is the same for all characters in this situation. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>This isn't really a fix... I could see the lower cons pretty easy before. The problem is where I run across an even con that has maxed stealth too... I could never find the person. The detection radius of an even con is so damn small there is no chance to set up a crit strike.<br><br>*sigh*<br><br>I'll give it a try before I bitch to loud but doesn't sound like they fixed anything.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usammyd11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sammyd11</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 8:54:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> Nice job Squink, you're a kick-ass team lead. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usquinkmcpoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Squink McPoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 9:07:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=18>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> The length of the horses that stand near the ticket vendors in hibernia is 130, so just about equal to 1.45b minimum detect radius.  My suggestion to Mythic is to double this radius for detect hidden characters.<br><br>Here is a pic for reference:<br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~sbeschei/horselength.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>X's mark measurements taken. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugamer4life.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gamer4Life</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 9:19:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1>  You actually think only doubling that length would fix it? With this info you know archers are now gonna make sure to also max stealth to 50 with items because when most population hits 50 we still will have to stumble onto them. <br><br> Personally I think a detect hidden type with maxed stealth should be able to spot non detect hidden stealthers a.k.a archers by about 5X that distance. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usquinkmcpoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Squink McPoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 9:57:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> Better to start s